The 158-test suite had two Windows-specific failures:

- `npm pack` could not start because Python subprocess resolution requires the `npm.cmd` shim.
- Node used case-sensitive path ordering while Python `WindowsPath` used case-folded ordering, so
  their Skill digests differed.

macOS and Ubuntu passed on the same commit. The fix is limited to executable resolution in the test
and Windows digest ordering in the Node CLI.
